\begin_inset Formula $f+g$
\end_inset

 is differentiable at zero.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
Not possible.
 According to the Algebraic Differentiability Theorem, since 
\begin_inset Formula $g$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(f+g\right)$
\end_inset

 are differentiable at zero, the function 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(\left(f+g\right)-g\right)$
\end_inset

 is also differentiable; however, 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\left(\left(f+g\right)-g\right)=f,
\]

\end_inset

which 
\begin_inset Formula $f$
\end_inset

 is not differentiable.
 This is a contradiction, and thus the request is impossible.
 
\end_layout

\end_deeper
